// Semantic direction:
// pipeline_def is the declaration of a data pipeline: its tasks, schedule, and dependencies.
// dag (Directed Acyclic Graph) represents the task execution order; dag_validate detects cycles.
// task_dp is one unit of work: an extract, SQL transform, Norscode script, or external job.
// task_sla is the maximum expected duration; breaches trigger alerts.
// dependency_dp specifies which task_instances must complete before a downstream task starts.
// dep_success requires upstream success; dep_all_done allows any terminal state.
// cross_pipeline_dep creates a dependency on a task in a different pipeline.
// run is one execution of the pipeline, identified by run_date and run_trigger.
// trigger_sensor starts a run when an external condition is met (file arrives, API responds).
// task_instance is one execution of one task within one run; it has its own state and log.
// xcom_push stores a value from a task; xcom_pull retrieves it in a downstream task.
// xcom enables lightweight data passing between tasks without writing to storage.
// sensor pokes an external system at sensor_interval until the condition is met or sensor_timeout_dp.
// file_sensor waits for a file to appear; sql_sensor waits for a query to return rows.
// external_task_sensor waits for a task_instance in another pipeline to reach dep_success.
// lineage tracks which datasets a task reads (edge_input) and writes (edge_output).
// lineage_graph connects datasets and tasks into a complete provenance record.
// impact_analysis finds all downstream datasets affected if a source dataset changes.
// root_cause_analysis traces a quality problem back to its originating task or dataset.
// data_catalog is the searchable inventory of all known datasets with schema, owner, and quality.
// dataset_quality_score summarizes freshness, completeness, and schema validity for a dataset.

// Primitive flow:
// define: pipeline_def(dag, schedule, owner) -> dag_validate (cycle check)
// schedule fires -> run created (run_id, run_date) -> topological_order_dp -> queue tasks
// task_instance: dequeue -> check dependency_dp (upstream ti_state) -> run if met
//   task runs -> xcom_push(result) -> ti_state=success
// sensor: sensor_poke every sensor_interval -> condition met -> mark success -> unblock downstream
// lineage: task starts -> record edge_input (datasets read) + edge_output (datasets written)
//   -> lineage_graph updated -> catalog_register new datasets
// impact_analysis: change in dataset X -> traverse lineage_graph downstream -> affected_datasets list

// This defines pipeline DAG orchestration, task instances, sensors, XCom data passing,
// data lineage tracking, impact analysis, and data catalog integration.
